## Overview

*Nature Communications* is a [peer-reviewed](/Peer_review), [open access](/Open_access), [scientific journal](/Scientific_journal) published by [Nature Portfolio](/Nature_Portfolio) since 2010. It is a multidisciplinary journal that covers the [natural sciences](/Natural_sciences), including [physics](/Physics), [chemistry](/Chemistry), [earth sciences](/Earth_sciences), [medicine](/Medicine), and [biology](/Biology). The journal has editorial offices in London, Berlin, New York City, and Shanghai.

The founding [editor-in-chief](/Editor-in-chief) was Lesley Anson, followed by Joerg Heber, [Magdalena Skipper](/Magdalena_Skipper), and Elisa De Ranieri. As of 2022, the editors are [Nathalie Le Bot](/Nathalie_Le_Bot) for health and clinical sciences, Stephane Larochelle for biological sciences, Enda Bergin for chemistry and biotechnology, and Prabhjot Saini for physics and earth sciences.

Starting October 2014, the journal only accepted submissions from authors willing to pay an [article processing charge](/Article_processing_charge). Until the end of 2015, part of the published submissions were only available to subscribers. In January 2016, all content became freely accessible.

Starting from 2017, the journal offers a deposition service to authors for [preprints](/Preprint) of articles "under consideration" as part of the submission process.

