## Abstracting and Indexing

The journal is abstracted and indexed in:

- [Science Citation Index Expanded](/Science_Citation_Index_Expanded)
- [Current Contents](/Current_Contents)/Agriculture, Biology & Environmental Sciences
- Current Contents/Life Sciences
- Current Contents/Physical, Chemical & Earth Sciences
- [The Zoological Record](/The_Zoological_Record)
- [BIOSIS Previews](/BIOSIS_Previews)
- [Chemical Abstracts Service](/Chemical_Abstracts_Service)
- [Index Medicus](/Index_Medicus)/[MEDLINE](/MEDLINE)/[PubMed](/PubMed)
- [Scopus](/Scopus)

According to the [Journal Citation Reports](/Journal_Citation_Reports), the journal has a 2024 [impact factor](/Impact_factor) of 15.7.

---

## Subjournals

In 2017, the creation of three "subjournals" under the Communications brand was announced: [Communications Biology](/Communications_Biology), [Communications Chemistry](/Communications_Chemistry), and [Communications Physics](/Communications_Physics). In the following years, several additional Communications journals were established: [Communications Materials](/Communications_Materials) in 2020, [Communications Earth & Environment](/Communications_Earth_%26_Environment) in 2020, [Communications Medicine](/Communications_Medicine) in 2021, Communications Engineering in 2022, and Communications Psychology in 2022.

These open-access journals offer a lower publication fee than *Nature Communications*, reflecting their more specialist remits. Manuscripts rejected by Nature Publishing Group journals can choose to transfer the manuscript together with reviewers' reports to the Communications-branded journals via an automated transfer service. Alternatively, authors may choose to request a fresh review.

